restaurants are devoted to vegetarian dishes, and by law all packaged food products in india are tagged with a green dot (vegetarian) or red dot (non-veg). veganism however is not a well-understood concept in india, and vegans may face a tougher time: milk products like cheese (paneer), yogurt (dahi) and clarified butter (ghee) are used extensively, and honey is also commonly used as a sweetener. milk in india is generally not pasteurized, and must be boiled before consumption. even non-vegetarians will soon note that due to the hindu taboo, beef is generally not served (except in the muslim and parsi 